}} As of the 2020 census, the population of the CDP was 78. The racial makeup of the CDP was 96.8% [[White (U.S. Census)|White]], 0.2% [[Native American (U.S. Census)|Native American]], and 2.3% from two or more races. [[Hispanic (U.S. Census)|Hispanic]] or [[Latino (U.S. Census)|Latino]] of any race were 0.7% of the population. [http://www.bestplaces.net/city/Stanford-Montana.aspx#]

As of the [[2010 United States Census|2010 census]] it had a population of 87.<ref name="Census 2010">{{Cite web| url=https://factfinder.census.gov/bkmk/table/1.0/en/DEC/10_SF1/G001/1600000US3030550| title=Geographic Identifiers: 2010 Census Summary File 1 (G001): Geyser CDP, Montana| publisher=U.S. Census Bureau| work=American Factfinder| accessdate=August 22, 2018| archive-url=https://archive.today/20200213092228/https://factfinder.census.gov/bkmk/table/1.0/en/DEC/10_SF1/G001/1600000US3030550| archive-date=February 13, 2020| url-status=dead}}</ref>

